        <h2>Edgar Allan Poe</h2>
        <p>
            Edgar Allan Poe was born in Boston on January 19, 1809, and died on
            October 7, 1849. He was an American writer, poet, editor and literary
            critic. Poe is best known for his poetry and short stories,
            particularly his tales of mystery and the macabre.
        </p>
        <p>
            He is widely regarded as a central figure of Romanticism in the United
            States and of American literature as a whole.
        </p>
    </div>

